-marvel-super-heroes-avengers-reassembled-clip/|archivedate=August 6, 2017}}</ref> voiced again by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"bwva\" />\n* Black Widow appears in the ''[[Spider-Man (2017 TV series)|Spider-Man]]'' episode \"Spider-Island\" Part 2, voiced again by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"bwva\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/the-threat-of-spider-island-brings-black-widow-to-marvel-s-spider-man|title=The Threat of Spider-Island Brings Black Widow to \u2018Marvel\u2019s Spider-Man\u2019|last=Goldman|first=Eric|publisher=Marvel.com|date=February 1, 2018|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422171708/https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/the-threat-of-spider-island-brings-black-widow-to-marvel-s-spider-man|archivedate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in ''[[Lego Marvel Super Heroes - Black Panther: Trouble in Wakanda]]'', voiced again by Laura Bailey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/see-the-teaser-for-lego-marvel-super-heroes-black-panther-trouble-in-wakanda|title=See the Teaser for \u2018LEGO Marvel Super Heroes \u2013 Black Panther: Trouble in Wakanda\u2019|last=Goldman|first=Eric|publisher=Marvel.com|date=May 2, 2018|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422170339/https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/see-the-teaser-for-lego-marvel-super-heroes-black-panther-trouble-in-wakanda|archivedate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in ''Marvel Future Avengers'', voiced by [[Mayumi Asano]] in Japanese and Laura Bailey in English.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n===Film===\n{{main|Natasha Romanoff (Marvel Cinematic Universe)}}\n[[File:Scarlett Johansson as Black Widow.jpg|thumbnail|upright|right|[[Scarlett Johansson]] as Natasha Romanoff in ''[[Iron Man 2]]'']]\n*In 2004, [[Lionsgate Entertainment]] announced that a ''Black Widow'' motion picture, featuring the Natasha Romanova version, was in the script stage by screenwriter-director [[David Hayter]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm|title=\"The Punisher II,\" \"Black Widow\" and Iron Fist\" Movie News|publisher=[[About.Com]]|date=March 2, 2004|accessdate=January 10, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607040255/http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm |archivedate=June 7, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Lionsgate subsequently dropped the project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/05/the-word-on-black-widow|title=The Word On Black Widow|author=Stax|website=IGN|date=June 5, 2006|accessdate=January 10, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826044253/http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/05/the-word-on-black-widow|archivedate=August 26, 2018}}</ref>\n*The Ultimate version of Black Widow appears in the ''[[Ultimate Avengers]]'' animated [[direct-to-video]] movie and its sequel, ''[[Ultimate Avengers 2]]'', voiced by [[Olivia d'Abo]].<ref name=\"bwva\" />\n*[[Scarlett Johansson]] portrays Natasha Romanoff / Black Widow in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].\n**Johansson made her debut appearance in ''[[Iron Man 2]]''.<ref name=\"Nikki Finke\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2-8763/|title=ANOTHER 'IRON MAN 2' DEAL: Scarlett Johannson To Replace Emily Blunt As Black Widow For Lousy Lowball Money|last=Finke|first=Nikki|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|date=March 11, 2009|accessdate=March 12, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918045450/https://deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2-8763/|archivedate=September 18, 2018}}</ref> She was cast after a scheduling conflict forced [[Emily Blunt]] to drop out of the part.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://hollywoodinsider.ew.com/2009/02/iron-man-2-will.html |title='Iron Man 2': Scarlett Johansson to replace Emily Blunt as Black Widow? |work=Entertainment Weekly |first=Nicole |last=Sperling |date=February 13, 2009 |accessdate=February 14, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217063340/http://hollywoodinsider.ew.com/2009/02/iron-man-2-will.html |archivedate=February 17, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n**Johansson reprised the role in ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' (2012),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |title=Marvel-ous Star Wattage: Actors Assemble For Comic-Con Panel Including 'The Avengers', 'Captain America', & 'Thor{{'-}} |date=July 24, 2010 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=July 25, 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zx6k1EnB?url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |archivedate=July 5, 2011 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' (2014),<ref name=\"WinterSoldier\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well-347013/|title=Five Actresses Testing For \u2018Captain America 2\u2019 Role; Black Widow Might Drop By As Well|last=Fleming Jr.|first=Mike|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|date=October 2, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322030738/https://deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well-347013/|archivedate=March 22, 2019|url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' (2015),<ref name=\"Johansson\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/scarlett-johansson-flaunts-curves-new-magazine-photo-shoot-article-1.1470378 |title=Scarlett Johansson flaunts curves in new magazine photo shoot, reveals details on 'The Avengers' sequel |last=Maresca |first=Rachel |newspaper=Daily News |date=September 29, 2013 |acce