arshall-black-widow/|archivedate=September 28, 2018}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in the 2013 direct-to-video animated film ''[[Iron Man: Rise of Technovore]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newsarama.com/10284-marvel-and-sony-announce-new-iron-man-animated-feature.html|title=Marvel and Sony Announce New IRON MAN Animated Feature|work=Newsarama|date=October 8, 2012|accessdate=April 21, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709094517/https://www.newsarama.com/10284-marvel-and-sony-announce-new-iron-man-animated-feature.html|archivedate=July 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/punisher-and-black-widow-to-star-in-new-marvel-animated-film/|title=Punisher and Black Widow to Star in New Marvel Animated Film|last=Melrose|first=Kevin|website=[[Comic Book Resources]]|date=January 15, 2013|accessdate=April 21, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214002930/https://www.cbr.com/punisher-and-black-widow-to-star-in-new-marvel-animated-film/|archivedate=February 14, 2019}}</ref> voiced by [[Clare Grant]].<ref name=\"bwva\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2013/03/second-trailer-for-marvel-anime-iron/|title=Second trailer for the Marvel anime Iron Man: Rise of Technovore|work=Flickering Myth|date=March 16, 2013|accessdate=February 13, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213064153/https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2013/03/second-trailer-for-marvel-anime-iron/|archivedate=February 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*Black Widow teams up with the Punisher in the animated film ''[[Avengers Confidential: Black Widow & Punisher]]'', voiced by [[Jennifer Carpenter]].<ref name=\"bwva\" /><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2014/01/21/marvels-avengers-confidential-black-widow-punisher-see-the-trailer-here-exclusive|title='Marvel's Avengers Confidential: Black Widow & Punisher': See the trailer here! EXCLUSIVE|last=Busis|first=Hillary|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 21, 2014|accessdate=January 21, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401074014/http://www.ew.com/article/2014/01/21/marvels-avengers-confidential-black-widow-punisher-see-the-trailer-here-exclusive|archivedate=April 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\n* Black Widow appears in the 2004 ''[[The Punisher (2004 video game)|Punisher]]'' video game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/games/the-punisher/35891/looking-back-at-2005s-the-punisher-videogame|title=Looking back at 2005's The Punisher Videogame|last=McManus|first=Kyle|work=Den of Geek|date=July 16, 2015|accessdate=February 13, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213123628/https://www.denofgeek.com/games/the-punisher/35891/looking-back-at-2005s-the-punisher-videogame|archivedate=February 13, 2019}}</ref> She appears in one level as a [[Non-player character|non-playable character]] (NPC) who fights alongside the Punisher. Black Widow was voiced by [[Saffron Henderson]].\n* Black Widow appears in the video game ''[[Marvel: Ultimate Alliance]]'', voiced by [[Nika Futterman]].<ref name=\"bwva\" /> She is an exclusive character in the [[PlayStation Portable]] (PSP) version, and in all other versions of the game as a non-playable character; a sub-plot in the game has various heroes investigating the possibility that she is a traitor, although Fury later confirms that she was just conducting a discreet investigation into [[Doctor Doom]]'s plans. A [[Mod (computer gaming)|mod]] available for the PC version of the game unlocks her as a playable character.\n* Black Widow appears in ''[[Spider-Man: Web of Shadows]]'', voiced by [[Salli Saffioti]].<ref name=\"bwva\" />\n* Nika Futterman reprises her role in ''[[Marvel: Ultimate Alliance 2]]'', appearing as a boss if the player chooses to fight for the anti-Registration side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2009/09/15/touring-the-marvel-ultimate-alliance-2-universe|title=Touring the Marvel: Ultimate Alliance 2 Universe |last=Schedeen|first=Jesse|website=[[IGN]]|date=September 14, 2009|accessdate=2012-06-11|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503142917/http://www.ign.com/articles/2009/09/15/touring-the-marvel-ultimate-alliance-2-universe?page=15|archivedate=May 3, 2016}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in the ''[[Iron Man 2 (video game)|Iron Man 2]]'' video game, voiced by Catherine Campion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yourindustryinsider.com/2011/10/actress-voiceover-artist-catherine-campion|title=Industry Pro: Actress/Voiceover Artist Catherine Campion|last=Yerrick Martin|first=Jenny|publisher=Your Industry Insider|date=October 5, 2011|accessdate=June 28, 2012|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120704163530/http://yourindustryinsider.com/2011/10/actress-voiceover-artist-catherine-campion/ |archivedate=July 4, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears as a playable character in the ''[[Marvel Super Hero Squad: The Infinity Gauntlet]]'' video game, voiced by [[Grey DeLisle]].<ref name=\"bwva\" />\n* Black Widow is a playable character in ''[[Marvel Super Hero Squad Online]]'', voiced by Laura Bailey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vg247.com/2012/02/08/marvel-super-hero-squad-online-to-be-fully-voiced/|title=Marvel Super Hero Squad Online to be fully voiced|last=Hillier|first=Brenna|website=[[VG247]]|date=February 8, 2012|accessdate=April 21, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906165318/http://www.vg247.com/2012/02/08/marvel-super-hero-squad-online-to-be-fully-voiced/|archivedate=September 6, 2015}}</ref>\n* Black Widow is a playable character in the [[Facebook]] game ''[[Marvel: Avengers Alliance]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamerant.com/avengers-alliance-facebook-characters/|title=Marvel's Avengers Alliance Adds X-Men & Fantastic Four Characters|last=Keyes|first=Rob|publisher=Gamerant|accessdate=April 1, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401003414/https://gamerant.com/avengers-alliance-facebook-characters/|archivedate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears as a Heroes vs Heralds card in ''[[Ultimate Marvel vs Capcom 3]]''. If Hawkeye defeats ''[[Street Fighter|Street Fighter's]]'' [[Crimson Viper]], he'll say, \"Black Widow you ain't.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eventhubs.com/news/2011/oct/19/cards-listing-heroes-heralds-mode-umvc3/|title=Early card listing for Heroes & Heralds mode in Ultimate Marvel vs. Capcom 3|last=Grey|first=Jonathan|publisher=Eventhubs|date=October 19, 2011|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150116065704/http://www.eventhubs.com/news/2011/oct/19/cards-listing-heroes-heralds-mode-umvc3/|archivedate=January 16, 2015}}</ref>\n* Black Widow is a playable character in ''[[Marvel Contest of Champions]]'', and was granted to every player for participation in the Ultron tie-in quests.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/avengers-age-of-ultron-marvel-contest-of-champions-1201478216/|title=\u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 Evil Robot Infests Mobile Game \u2018Marvel Contest of Champions\u2019|last=Spangler|first=Todd|magazine=Variety|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=April 1, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042737/https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/avengers-age-of-ultron-marvel-contest-of-champions-1201478216/|archivedate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears as a playable character in the 2012 [[fighting game]] ''[[Marvel Avengers: Battle for Earth]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2012/10/19/3524806/marvel-avengers-battle-for-earth-line-up-include-black-widow-doctor|title=Marvel Avengers Battle for Earth line-up includes Black Widow, Doctor Doom, Iron Man, Loki and more|last=Lien|first=Tracey|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|date=October 19, 2012|accessdate=April 23, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422231009/https://www.polygon.com/2012/10/19/3524806/marvel-avengers-battle-for-earth-line-up-include-black-widow-doctor|archivedate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow is available as downloadable content for the game ''[[LittleBigPlanet]]'' as part of \"Marvel Costume Kit 5\".<ref name=\"LittleBigPlanetMCK5\">{{cite web |url=http://us.playstation.com/games-and-media/add-ons/littlebigplanet-2-marvel-heroes-costume-pack-5.html |title=Marvel Costume Kit 5 |publisher=[[Sony]] |accessdate=December 30, 2012 |archivedate=December 22, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222053229/http://us.playstation.com/games-and-media/add-ons/littlebigplanet-2-marvel-heroes-costume-pack-5.html |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref>\n* Black Widow is featured on the A-Force table in [[Zen Pinball 2]], as part of the \"Women of Power\" DLC pack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/282205/Marvels_Women_of_Power_Pinball_Pack_Hits_Zenrsquos_PinballPlatforms_Today.php|title=Marvel's Women of Power Pinball Pack Hits Zen's Pinball Platforms Today|website=[[Gamasutra]]|date=September 27, 2016|accessdate=April 13, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617043124/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/282205/Marvels_Women_of_Power_Pinball_Pack_Hits_Zenrsquos_PinballPlatforms_Today.php|archivedate=June 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ps4blog.net/2016/11/ps4-marvels-women-of-power-two-pack-review/|title=[PS4] Marvel\u2019s Women of Power Pinball Pack Review|last=Corson|first=Tracy|publisher=PS4Blog|date=November 1, 2016|accessdate=April 13, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627142423/http://www.ps4blog.net/2016/11/ps4-marvels-women-of-power-two-pack-review/|archivedate=June 27, 2017}}</ref>\n* Black Widow is a playable character in the [[MMORPG]] ''[[Marvel Heroes (video game)|Marvel Heroes]]'',<ref name=\"MarvelHeroesMMORPG\">{{cite web |url=https://www.marvelheroes.com/news/news-articles/black-widow-joins-marvel-heroes |title=Black Widow joins Marvel Heroes |publisher=Gazillion Entertainment |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140311105209/https://www.marvelheroes.com/news/news-articles/black-widow-joins-marvel-heroes |date=May 22, 2012 |archivedate=March 11, 2014 |accessdate=November 25, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref> voiced by [[Julianne Buescher]].<ref name=\"btva\">{{cite web|title=Voice of Black Widow - Marvel Universe franchise <nowiki>|</nowiki> Behind The Voice Actors|url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/characters/Marvel-Universe/Black-Widow/|website=Behind The Voice Actors|accessdate=September 18, 2018|postscript=. Check mark indicates role has been confirmed using screenshots of closing credits and other reliable sources}}</ref>\n* Black Widow is a playable character in ''[[Lego Marvel Super Heroes]]'' voiced by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"LegoMarvelvideogame\">{{cite web |url=http://marvel.com/news/story/19916/lego_marvel_super_heroes_on_the_way |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes On the Way |publisher=[[Marvel Comics|Marvel.com]] |date=January 8, 2013 |accessdate=January 8, 2013 |archivedate=January 9, 2013 |archiveurl=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20130109193530/http://marvel.com/news/story/19916/lego_marvel_super_heroes_on_the_way |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> She serves as one of the main story characters.\n* Black Widow is a playable character in ''Marvel Avengers Alliance Tactics''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/the-next-avengers-game-takes-on-turn-based-tactics-1575272820|title=The Next Avengers Game Takes On Turn-Based Tactics|last=Fahey|first=Mike|publisher=Kotaku|date=May 12, 2014|accessdate=April 1, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401003414/https://kotaku.com/the-next-avengers-game-takes-on-turn-based-tactics-1575272820|archivedate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears as a playable character in'' [[Disney Infinity: Marvel Super Heroes]]'' and ''[[Disney Infinity 3.0]]'', again voiced by Laura Bailey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo-insider.com/iron-man-black-widow-disney-infinity-marvel-super-heroes/|title=Iron Man and Black Widow deploy in Disney Infinity: Marv