Cinematic Universe)}}\n[[File:Scarlett Johansson as Black Widow.jpg|thumbnail|upright|right|[[Scarlett Johansson]] as Natasha Romanoff in ''[[Iron Man 2]]'']]\n*In 2004, [[Lionsgate Entertainment]] announced that a ''Black Widow'' motion picture, featuring the Natasha Romanova version, was in the script stage by screenwriter-director [[David Hayter]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm|title=\"The Punisher II,\" \"Black Widow\" and Iron Fist\" Movie News|publisher=[[About.Com]]|date=March 2, 2004|accessdate=January 10, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607040255/http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm |archivedate=June 7, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Lionsgate subsequently dropped the project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/05/the-word-on-black-widow|title=The Word On Black Widow|author=Stax|website=IGN|date=June 5, 2006|accessdate=January 10, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826044253/http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/05/the-word-on-black-widow|archivedate=August 26, 2018}}</ref>\n*The Ultimate version of Black Widow appears in the ''[[Ultimate Avengers]]'' animated [[direct-to-video]] movie and its sequel, ''[[Ultimate Avengers 2]]'', voiced by [[Olivia d'Abo]].<ref name=\"bwva\" />\n*[[Scarlett Johansson]] portrays Natasha Romanoff / Black Widow in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].\n**Johansson made her debut appearance in ''[[Iron Man 2]]''.<ref name=\"Nikki Finke\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2-8763/|title=ANOTHER 'IRON MAN 2' DEAL: Scarlett Johannson To Replace Emily Blunt As Black Widow For Lousy Lowball Money|last=Finke|first=Nikki|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|date=March 11, 2009|accessdate=March 12, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918045450/https://deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2-8763/|archivedate=September 18, 2018}}</ref> She was cast after a scheduling conflict forced [[Emily Blunt]] to drop out of the part.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://hollywoodinsider.ew.com/2009/02/iron-man-2-will.html |title='Iron Man 2': Scarlett Johansson to replace Emily Blunt as Black Widow? |work=Entertainment Weekly |first=Nicole |last=Sperling |date=February 13, 2009 |accessdate=February 14, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217063340/http://hollywoodinsider.ew.com/2009/02/iron-man-2-will.html |archivedate=February 17, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n**Johansson reprised the role in ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' (2012),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |title=Marvel-ous Star Wattage: Actors Assemble For Comic-Con Panel Including 'The Avengers', 'Captain America', & 'Thor{{'-}} |date=July 24, 2010 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=July 25, 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zx6k1EnB?url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |archivedate=July 5, 2011 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' (2014),<ref name=\"WinterSoldier\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well-347013/|title=Five Actresses Testing For \u2018Captain America 2\u2019 Role; Black Widow Might Drop By As Well|last=Fleming Jr.|first=Mike|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|date=October 2, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322030738/https://deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well-347013/|archivedate=March 22, 2019|url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' (2015),<ref name=\"Johansson\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/scarlett-johansson-flaunts-curves-new-magazine-photo-shoot-article-1.1470378 |title=Scarlett Johansson flaunts curves in new magazine photo shoot, reveals details on 'The Avengers' sequel |last=Maresca |first=Rachel |newspaper=Daily News |date=September 29, 2013 |accessdate=September 29, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929050049/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/scarlett-johansson-flaunts-curves-new-magazine-photo-shoot-article-1.1470378 |archivedate=September 29, 2013 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' (2016),<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://deadline.com/2014/11/daniel-bruhl-captain-america-robert-downey-jr-chris-evans-1201284648/|title=Daniel Bruhl To Play Villain In 'Captain America: Civil War'|last=Fleming, Jr|first=Mike|magazine=Deadline|date=November 14, 2014|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329002544/https://deadline.com/2014/11/daniel-bruhl-captain-america-robert-downey-jr-chris-evans-1201284648/|archivedate=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' (2018),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/897044/ranking-the-avengers-infinity-war-makeovers|title=Ranking the Avengers: Infinity War Makeovers, From Captain America's Beard to Blonde Black Widow|last=Heller|first=Corinne|publisher=[[E! News]]|date=November 29, 2017|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705063518/https://www.eonline.com/news/897044/ranking-the-avengers-infinity-war-makeovers|archivedate=July 5, 2018}}</ref> a cameo in a post-credits scene of ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'' (2019),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/7/18255336/captain-marvel-post-credits-scene-avengers-endgame-flerken-alien-cat-goose-tesseract |title=One of Captain Marvel's post-credits scenes is great news for Avengers: Endgame |last=Robinson |first=Tasha |work=