es/marvel-vs-capcom-infinites-dlc-characters-announce/1100-6453396/|title=Marvel Vs. Capcom: Infinite DLC Characters Announced, Include Venom And Monster Hunter|first=Kevin|last=Knezevic|publisher=[[Gamespot]]|date=September 18, 2017|accessdate=October 30, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213061956/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/marvel-vs-capcom-infinite-dlc-characters-announced/1100-6453396/|archivedate=December 13, 2018}}</ref> voiced by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"btva\"/>\n* Black Widow appears as a playable character in ''Marvel Powers United VR'', again voiced by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"btva\"/>\n* Black Widow appears as a playable character in ''[[Marvel Ultimate Alliance 3: The Black Order]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/14/all-the-confirmed-characters-in-marvel-ultimate-alliance-3|title=All the Confirmed Characters in Marvel Ultimate Alliance 3|last=Downey|first=Meg|website=[[IGN]]|date=January 14, 2019|accessdate=April 23, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190318104751/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/14/all-the-confirmed-characters-in-marvel-ultimate-alliance-3|archivedate=March 18, 2019}}</ref> voiced again by Laura Bailey.<ref name=\"btva\"/>\n* Black Widow will be a playable character in the 2020 ''[[Avengers (2020 video game)|Avengers]]'' game, voiced again by Laura Bailey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/square-enix-gives-us-our-first-look-at-marvel-s-avengers-556958.phtml|title=Square Enix gives us our first look at Marvel's Avengers|last=Glagowski|first=Peter|website=[[Destructoid]]|date=June 10, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718220234/https://www.destructoid.com/square-enix-gives-us-our-first-look-at-marvel-s-avengers-556958.phtml|archivedate=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Motion comics===\n* Black Widow appears in the ''[[Spider-Woman (Jessica Drew)|Spider-Woman]]'' [[motion comics]] voiced by JoEllen Anklam. During this appearance she is masquerading as [[Black Widow (Yelena Belova)|Yelena Belova]].<ref name=\"bwvayelena\">{{cite web|url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/characters/Marvel-Universe/Black-Widow-Yelena-Belova/|title=Voice Of Black Widow / Yelena Belova \u2013 Marvel Universe <nowiki>|</nowiki> Behind The Voice Actors|website=Behind The Voice Actors|date=|accessdate=April 23, 2019|postscript=. Check marks indicates role has been confirmed using screenshots of closing credits and other reliable sources}}</ref>\n\n===Live performances===\n* Black Widow appears in ''[[Marvel Universe: LIVE!]]'' as a member of the Avengers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://comicsalliance.com/superheroines-concept-art-marvel-universe-live/ |title=New Images Reveal The Superheroines Of 'Marvel Universe Live!'|last=Wilson|first=Matt|work=Comics Alliance|date=November 27, 2013|accessdate=July 17, 2014|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717040913/http://comicsalliance.com/superheroines-concept-art-marvel-universe-live/ |archivedate=July 17, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Former motorcycle racer [[Louise Forsley]] has portrayed the character as of 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/theater-art/2015/08/23/now-marvel-hero-former-bike-racer-enjoying-her-superpowers/1YwWeLOM1yWSkcsGoIP9qM/story.html|title=Now a Marvel hero, former bike racer is enjoying her superpowers - The Boston Globe|last=Abren|first=Mallory|website=[[Boston Globe]]|date=August 24, 2015|accessdate=April 23, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616154031/https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/theater-art/2015/08/23/now-marvel-hero-former-bike-racer-enjoying-her-superpowers/1YwWeLOM1yWSkcsGoIP9qM/story.html|archivedate=June 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Novels===\n* There are two Black Widow books in the Black Widow YA series, by [[Margaret Stohl]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://ew.com/article/2015/10/14/forever-red-margaret-stohl-ew-review/|title='Forever Red' by Margaret Stohl: EW Review|last=Towers|first=Andrea|magazine=EW.com|date=November 14, 2015|accessdate=April 23, 2019|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012135155/https://ew.com/article/2015/10/14/forever-red-margaret-stohl-ew-review/|archivedate=October 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/865638682/YA-author-Margaret-Stohl-helps-create-new-Marvel-superhero-in-6Black-Widow-Forever-Red7.html?pg=all|title=YA author Margaret Stohl helps create new Marvel superhero in 'Black Widow: Forever Red'|last=Loftus|first=Hikari|newspaper=[[Deseret News]]|date=2015-10-10|accessdate=April 3, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181220211143/https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865638682/YA-author-Margaret-Stohl-helps-create-new-Marvel-superhero-in-6Black-Widow-Forever-Red7.html|archivedate=December 20, 2018}}</ref>\n** ''[[Black Widow: Forever Red]]'' (2015)\n** ''[[Black Widow: Red Vengeance]]'' (2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.marvel.com/comics/26877/black_widow_taking_red_vengeance/|title=Black Widow: Taking Red Vengeance|last=Cooke|first=Sarah|website=Marvel|date=October 18, 2016|accessdate=October 30, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107022346/https://news.marvel.com/comics/26877/black_widow_taking_red_vengeance/|archivedate=November 7, 2017}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in the [[prose]] [[novel]] adaptation of the event comic ''[[The Death of Captain America]]''.<ref>{{cite book |author =Hama, Larry |url =https://books.google.com/books?id=s-veDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT4&dq=marvel+prose+novel&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_-7zQs43TAhXDWSwKHUR9BrAQ6AEIKjAC#v=snippet&q=black%20widow&f=false |title =The Death Of Captain America Prose Novel |date =November 18, 2014 |page = |isbn =978-0785189978 |publisher =Marvel |via=Google Books}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in the [[prose]] [[novel]] adaptation of the event comic ''[[Civil War (comics)|Civil War]]''.<ref>{{cite book |author =Moore, Stuart |url =https://books.google.com/books?id=s-veDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT4&dq=marvel+prose+novel&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_-7zQs43TAhXDWSwKHUR9BrAQ6AEIKjAC#v=snippet&q=black%20widow&f=false |title =Civil War Illustrated Prose Novel |date =March 15, 2016 |page = |isbn =978-0785195863 |publisher =Marvel |via=Google Books}}</ref>\n* Black Widow appears in ''Avengers: Everybody Wants To Rule The World'' which is a tie-in to ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://marvel.com/news/comics/23173/avengers_everybody_wants_to_rule_the_world_-_coming_in_2015|title=''Avengers: Everybody Wants to Rule the World'' - Coming in 2015|first= Paul |last= Montgomery|date= August 28, 2014|publisher= Marvel Comics|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20151119234654/http://marvel.com/news/comics/23173/avengers_everybody_wants_to_rule_the_world_-_coming_in_2015|archivedate= November 19, 2015|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe Black Widow was ranked as the 176th greatest comic book character in ''[[Wizard (magazine)|Wizard]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://herochat.com/forum/index.php?topic=170859.0 |title=Wizard's top 200 characters. External link consists of a forum site summing up the top 200 characters of Wizard Magazine since the real site that contains the list is broken. |magazine=[[Wizard (magazine)|Wizard magazine]]. |accessdate=May 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608020121/http://herochat.com/forum/index.php?topic=170859.0 |archivedate=June 8, 2011 |df=mdy }}</ref> [[IGN]] also ranked her as the 74th greatest comic book character stating that wherever conspiracy and treachery are afoot, you can expect the Black Widow to appear to save the day,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ign.com/lists/comic-book-heroes/74|title=Black Widow is number 74|website=IGN|accessdate=May 11, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723200314/http://www.ign.com/lists/comic-book-heroes/74|archivedate=July 23, 2018}}</ref> and as #42 on their list of the \"Top 50 Avengers\".<ref>{{cite web |date=April 30, 2012 |title=The Top 50 Avengers |url=http://www.ign.com/lists/avengers/42|website=[[IGN]]|accessdate=July 28, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707134421/http://www.ign.com/lists/avengers/42|archivedate=July 7, 2018}}</ref> She was ranked 31st in ''[[Comics Buyer's Guide]]'s'' \"100 Sexiest Women in Comics\" list.<ref>{{cite book|last=Frankenhoff|first=Brent|authorlink=Brent Frankenhoff|title=Comics Buyer's Guide Presents: 100 Sexiest Women in Comics|publisher=[[Krause Publications]]|year=2011|page=27|url=|isbn=1-4402-2988-0}}</ref>\n\n==Collected editions==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|'''#'''\n|'''Title'''\n|'''Material Collected'''\n|'''Pages'''\n|'''Publication Date'''\n|'''ISBN'''\n|-\n|\n|''Black Widow: The Sting of the Widow'' || ''[[Tales of Suspense]]'' #52, ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' #86, ''[[Amazing Adventures]]'' vol. 2 #1\u20138, and ''[[Daredevil (Marvel Comics series)|Daredevil]]'' #81 \n| || September 2, 2009||{{ISBNT|0-7851-3794-7}}\n|-\n|\n|''Black Widow: Deadly Origin'' || ''Black Widow: Deadly Origin'' #1\u20134 \n| || March 17, 2010||{{ISBNT|0-7851-4301-7}}\n|-\n|\n|''Black Widow: Web of Intrigue'' || ''[[Marvel Fanfare]]'' #10\u201313, ''[[Bizarre Adventures]]'' #25, and ''Black Widow: The Coldest War'' \n| || April 7, 2010||{{ISBNT|0-7851-4474-9}}\n|-\n|\n|''Black Widow & The Marvel Girls'' || ''Black Widow & The Marvel Girls'' #1-4 \n| || April 21, 2010||{{ISBNT|978-0785146995}}\n|-\n|\n|''Hawkeye & Mockingbird / Black Widow: Widowmaker'' || ''Solo Avengers'' #16\u201318, ''Widowmaker'' #1\u20134 \n| || April 20, 2011||{{ISBNT|0-7851-5205-9}}\n|-\n|\n|''Marvel's the Avengers: Black Widow Strikes'' || ''Marvel's the Avengers: Black Widow Strikes'' #1-3 \n| || September 19, 2012||{{ISBNT|978-0785165682}}\n|-\n|\n|''Captain America and Black Widow'' || ''Captain America and Black Widow 636-640'' \n| || February 26, 2013||{{ISBNT|978-0785165286}}\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" |Volume 1 & 2\n|-\n|\n|''Black Widow: 